{
  "texts": [
    "The final correlations between the various bits of the MASK are provided in Appendix F.Another addition to the masks for DR5 is the inclusion of a 'strong-selection' mask, which is designed to remove areas of the survey where there have been pathological photometric measurement failures within GAAP.",
    "These failures are related to the difference in the PSF sizes between the detection r-band images and the other bands, as discussed in Sect. 6.2.",
    "As discussed, A170, page 26 of 54 Wright, A. H., et al.",
    ": A&A, 686, A170 (2024) Reserved, unused this effect led initially to the requirement of measuring fluxes in apertures with two minimum radii (see Sect. 3.6), but in some cases even the use of the larger aperture is not sufficient to stop GAAP from being unable to measure a flux.",
    "As these failures are related to the size of the object aperture, when such failures occur, they preferentially affect the smallest objects first."
  ]
}